5|$|Harry and the Potters are an American {{rock band}} known for {{spawning}} {{the genre of}} wizard rock. Founded in Norwood, Massachusetts in 2002, the group is primarily composed of brothers Joe and Paul DeGeorge, who both perform under <b>the</b> <b>persona</b> of the title character from the Harry Potter book series. Harry and the Potters {{are known for their}} elaborate live performances, and have developed a cult following within the Harry Potter fandom.|$|E
5|$|Prior to its {{popularity}} in the west, the game was a major franchise in Japan, having sold over 4 million units by 2003. By 2016, the series has sold approximately 14 million packaged and digital units worldwide, with the combined series grouped within the Megami Tensei franchise accounting for 7.2 million and <b>the</b> <b>Persona</b> series accounting for 6.9 million. Megami Tensei is one of Atlus' best-selling and most important franchises.|$|E
