5000|$|Marginalization is {{the being}} or being made {{socially}} marginal through {{a denial of}} power. Third persona can be distinguished from marginalization because <b>the</b> Third <b>Persona</b> is not only denied power and public voice, but is, at a basic level, denied consideration or recognition by those in power. While marginalization is an overt removal of power, <b>the</b> third <b>persona</b> suffers from an innate or unrecognized removal from power. Those persons {{who make up the}} body of <b>the</b> third <b>persona</b> may not be even considered to exist. Whereas the marginalized have a suppressed voice—a [...] "marginal" [...] voice—those of <b>the</b> third <b>persona</b> have no voice.|$|R
